      public void testStartGame()

    • testSetIndex

      public void testSetIndex()
      Tests if setIndex is working by showing the value of index (0, 3) is "x" before we call the method and has a value of "1" after we call the method with the parameters set to change row 1 column 4 (index 0, 3) to a value of "1".

    • testGameComplete

      public void testGameComplete()
      Tests to make sure gameComplete only returns true if the parameter is set to 0 and not another number.

    • testSetRow

      public void testSetRow()
      Tests if setRow is working by creating a String array with a set of 9 values to replace the ones currently in the Sudoku puzzle. The test does a check of each of the indices that should have been replaced and checks if the value is what was given by the String array.

    • testSetEqual

      public void testSetEqual()
      Test to check if setEqual method actually sets the users puzzle equal to the master key.

    • testCheckCorrect

      public void testCheckCorrect()
      Test to see if the testCorrect method is able to tell that the master and user puzzles are equal when they are set that way. If there are no mistakes in the puzzle, the mistakes variable should remain at 0, allowing us to test the validity of the method.
